name: Kourovka, Sverdlovsk Oblast
summary:
Kourovka (Russian: Коу́ровка) is a settlement in Pervouralsk Urban okrug in Sverdlovsk Oblast, Russia. Population:  315 (2010 census); 449 (2002 census); 

Kourovka was founded in 1908 or 1909 as a railroad town near a station of the Trans-Siberian railway. It bears its name from the Kourov log ravine, named after Kour, peasant of the nearby Chusovaya sloboda who lived in late 17th century. In its turn, Kourovka is the namesake of a street in Yekaterinburg, a minor planet 4964 Kourovka and Kouro
